caption:
In the last week I’ve had people booking in for the flu shot and leaving the clinic without one :syringe: Why? Firstly, the Government funded vaccines for anyone over 65, patients with a chronic medical condition (like asthma or diabetes), women who are pregnant are not yet available to us. Secondly, you need to time the shot so it works!! :flushed_face: Last year we had a HORRIFIC flu season with deaths and huge numbers of affected people. If I jab you today the flu shot effectiveness starts to reduce after 3 to 4 months which means you may not be covered in peak flu season- August! I’ve counselled many patients this week to wait if possible until April to get their shot - it means they’ll be covered when the flu is thriving in the community. Remember if you want the shot you need a new one each year- the virus strains covered in the vaccine change each year because the virus is clever; it keeps mutating and changing :face_screaming_in_fear: So despite all the hype about the flu shot- you might just need to wait a little bit before you get jabbed! FYI Miss S, Will and I will get ours towards the end of April :smiling_face: Tag someone who might find this helpful :thumbs_up_medium-dark_skin_tone: See you summer, Winter I feel you coming :crying_cat_face::snowflake:

TY for sharing Jayliana's story with us @hez_lynn_ . ⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
"2 years ago today.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
This was one of the worst days of my life. Jayliana had a drs appt in the morning, we went...and 20-30 minutes later she started turning blue. She didn't look herself. I called the dr and he assured me that it was normal. Well my father didn't think so. He drove us an hour away to the nearest children's hospital. I remember stopping for gas, and he checked Jaylee and he got in the truck and floored it. I knew something was wrong. He grabbed her carseat for me when we got to the hospital and wouldn't let me see her, he ran in and showed them at the counter the baby. A nurse comes running from the other side and takes her out the seat and starts screaming for help. Next thing I know codes are being screamed and all available drs and nurses were running with my baby to a room. My daughter was blue, ice cold, limp and unresponsive. They did CPR and it didn't work, they then shoved a tube down her throat and were breathing for her, they brought over a huge heater and blew the hot air on her little body, then about 30 mins later they decided to shock her. She was shocked 3x. They got pulse! They all cheered and hugged. They were still manually breathing for her. She was taken up to I.C.U and placed on life support. ⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
This day changed my daughter's life forever. My baby recieved the DTAP vaccine at that drs visit. We didnt know it was a vaccine injury until 2 weeks later when she recieved the HIB and she had back to back seizures and was air lifted to the hospital and she got worse and was placed on life support again.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
Jayliana just turned 2 years old and unfortunately is hospitalized every month. We just found out that she has the MTHFR gene mutation too.
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
Picture on top is the morning of the drs appt, before we went. And the bottom is after the appt and just a couple hours later."

A limit of 10ng of residual DNA has been set for vaccines. Research has shown that they contain much more than this, though the limit is not for diploid cell lines.

In almost every state you can claim religious exemption from vaccines when sending your kids to school except In California, Mississippi and West Virginia. In every other state you can claim religious exemption. You don’t go to a doctor to get an exemption form or a school. You simply write a letter and submit it with your school application instead of your vaccine records. They can’t deny you. That would be denying you your constitutional right to practice religion your way. You don’t need to be a member of a church or a certain religion. If they try to deny you then you can sue them. So don’t let no one scare you into getting vaccines. You can google how to write a religious exemption letter and find many examples. It’s not hard. The system hopes parents are uneducated in the matter and then they can scare them into getting their kids vaccinated. Also when doctors try to make you sign papers saying you refused vaccines always sign (under duress) next to your name :winking_face::winking_face::winking_face: Dont let them intimidate you. Vaccines have aborted cells in them which is not what God wants us injecting in our kids. They have heavy metals and all types of toxins God didn’t intend for us to inject in our body. Back in 2016 they tried to question my original letter. I let them know my rights and they had no choice but to let my kids attend. That’s why it’s important we don’t let what happened in California with mandatory vaccines happen in other states. It’s coming with #HealthyPeople2020 so beware. Our program requires a two-step PPD every year. // What does this do? //
The two-step PPD test is used to detect individuals with past TB infection who now have diminished skin test reactivity. This procedure reduces the likelihood that a boosted reaction is later interpreted as a new infection. caption: "You don't own your body..." :right_arrow::right_arrow: At 18 months, Rio got his last major vaccination until he is 4 yrs old:glowing_star::glowing_star::glowing_star:. Getting a baby vaccinated is an awful experience --- but one that has gotten a little easier for me after reading this book that dives deep into the  vaccination debate. In :right_arrow:On Immunity:left_arrow:, the skeptical and concerned mother/journalist Eula Biss does all the research and interviews that you wish you had the time and resources to do. And while the decision to vaccinate is up you, Biss (and me too) ultimately lands on the side that the benefits of vaccinations far outweigh their potential risks. If you have any doubts about vaccinations (as I did too!) I highly recommend you give this thoughtful book a read. Because choosing whether or not you vaccinate yourself or your children has implications that travel beyond your body, and could very much impact the lives of the young, the elderly, and the vulnerable.  It's our social responsibility to at the very least make an informed decision. #vaccinate #interdependence #innoculate #eulabiss #onimmunity #forthegreatergood #eulabiss #society#community #health #vaccinateyourkids #societalresponsibility #interdependence #youdontownyourbody

caption:
Can we talk flu shots for a minute? I grew up in the 80’s and never got a flu shot my entire life until I was pregnant with my first child. I got the flu vaccine the years I was pregnant with my children, and the winter when my daughter was only 3 months old. Each of my children got the vaccine their first year of life, and that’s it. My son, who is 4, got the flu for the first time this week, and I had a mother try to “flu shot shame me” this morning. What is so wrong with our kids getting the flu? I got the flu maybe twice as a kid. Yes, it sucked. Yes, I got a fever and threw up a couple times, but so what! My body beat it, and is stronger for it. My son threw up 3 times the first day, and has been fine since. He’s running a fever, but other than that is happily watching movies and snuggling his mama. We went to the doctor yesterday for the viral swab and they confirmed it’s influenza A. They also tried to push Tamiflu, which we took home, but haven’t given him since we personally feel it’s better to let his body do the work and build the immunities. Other than the flu being inconvenient (missing work, missing school, etc), why are we as a country so terrified to let our children get sick and build their own immunities? Don’t get me wrong, I am all for single dose vaccines for the things that matter, but the flu vaccine is 30-60% effective against a few strains of the virus when there’s hundreds out there. I’m not on board. 
Let’s become strong again! Let’s beat sickness and viruses with our own strong bodies. Sometimes life throws us curveballs like the flu. Knock it out of the park and keep on going! .
....
.

caption:
"As women have children later and later in life, the need to take medications during pregnancy is on the rise. Unfortunately, because very few studies have been conducted on how medications work in pregnant women, we’re really in the dark as to what kind of effects they have on both women and their fetuses. 
But new legislation aimed to address this lack of knowledge has finally been proposed. The problem is we actually have no idea how most medicines affect pregnant women or her fetus.

One study reported that in 2008, more than 90 percent of pregnant women took at least one medication, prescription or over-the-counter, at some point during their pregnancy.

But women’s bodies change drastically during pregnancy and those changes affect the way the body responds to and breaks down medications. Blood volume and heart rate increase, movement through the gastrointestinal tract slows, the kidneys filter the blood faster, and enzymes in the liver that break down medications become more or less active depending on the enzyme..." #prescription #medication #pregnancyannouncement #tylenol #aspirin #pills #healthybaby #healthy #health #pregnant #safety #pregnantbelly #pharmacist #pharma #liver #vaccination #reaction #blood #immunesystem #tigernuts #pineapple #liver #knowledgeispower #newlife #genderreveal #pregnancyloss #pregnantlife #babyontheway

caption:
You know what bums me out more than Pixar Fest ending? The still-prevalent misconception that autism is caused by vaccines.
:cross_mark::woman_gesturing_NO_light_skin_tone::cross_mark:
The idea that vaccines cause autism came from a 1998 journal publication with only 12 subjects, all of whom had been vaccinated (I.e., no control group). In addition to other flaws in the research design, one of the primary researchers was paid over $500,000 by people who wanted him to publish ANY results claiming that there was a link between autism and vaccines for their own personal gain. Cases like this are the reason that science has ethics review boards, why scientists have to disclose any conflicts of interest, why we need strong peer review processes, and why replicating studies is so important.
:money_with_wings:
Since the 1998 study, over a dozen additional studies have been conducted and have found no substantive correlations between vaccines and autism. This means that children who received vaccines do not have any higher likelihood of being autistic than children who did not receive their vaccines.
:chart_decreasing::books::chart_increasing:
Furthermore, many people might think that vaccines cause autism because being vaccinated and diagnosed as autistic happen around the same time in a child’s life. This is the best example of “correlation not causation” - just because two things happen at the same time does not mean that one caused the other. That would be like saying deciding to get a churro caused you to be able to get a FastPass for your favorite ride - just because those two things happened at the same time doesn’t mean that one led to the other. But churros are like vaccines in one way: I recommend that everyone get them.
:mouse_face::castle::roller_coaster:
The cause of autism is still unknown but most evidence suggests it is due to mutations in genes that control neural development. These mutated genes can be inherited or occur during fetal development.
:woman_scientist_medium-dark_skin_tone::man_scientist_light_skin_tone::pregnant_woman_medium-light_skin_tone::breast-feeding_medium-light_skin_tone:
Check out resources on aap.org and pbs.org for more!

caption:
The #eVIN temperature loggers are SIM-enabled devices that make sure vaccines are stored at the recommended temperatures. Vaccines are stored at an optimal temperature-- between 2-8°C -- to maintain their safety and potency. Temperature data is recorded every ten minutes and updated at an interval of sixty minutes on the server via General Packet Radio Service (GPRS). In case of temperature breach, the logger alarms and sends email and SMS alerts to responsible cold chain technicians and managers.
The eVIN initiative is being implemented the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare with support from the United Nations Development Programme in India.

caption: Just finished a shift at work and today i saw a baby who had pertussis (whooping cough). Baby was struggling to breathe and due to the coughing he kept choking, gagging and was unable to keep his milk or fluids down as he was vomiting with the coughing fits. He was not up to date with his immunisations as his mum kept postponing them due to fear relating to something she had seen on social media and because he wasn’t up to date with his immunisations he came in contact with someone in his family who had pertussis a couple of week’s ago and he now has it. This is not the first time we have seen this where parents are reluctant to immunise due to things they read on social media. This is the risk of social media. Some social influencers with a lot of following are using their social media platforms to flood social media with misinformed information relating to immunisations and are encouraging parents to be “antivax” or against vaccinations without any real evidence behind their actions. Every parent is entitled to informed consent but I urge parents to please do your research before you make a decision not to vaccinate your children as your choice can affect their health and well-being as well as the wellbeing of your community. This is of significance especially if you live in an area such as our community (ie south auckland) where these diseases or infections still exist. Every parent has a right to accept or decline vaccinating their child and we as health professionals will respect that decision but just please ask your doctor or clinic for more information about immunisations or how to access evidence based information rather than just making a decision based on what you read on someone’s social media post #vaccination #immunisation #vax #parents #childhealth #nz #health #medicine #children #informed #prochoice #mum #dad #vax

caption:
Getting ready for school? T.H.E. patients ages 4-17 can get immunized for free at our Back-to-School Immunization Clinic happening Saturday, August 12 and 19, from 9AM to 12PM at T.H.E. at 3834 S. Western Avenue in Los Angeles. Supplies are limited. First come, first serve. Bring school vaccination cards. 
Many vaccine-preventable diseases can easily spread in child care and school settings. Protecting your children from preventable diseases will help keep them healthy and in school.
• Schools are prone to outbreaks of infectious diseases, and school-age children can further spread disease to their families and others with whom they come in contact. • When a child comes down with an illness such as whooping cough, chickenpox or the flu, he or she may miss a lot of school while recovering – and somebody will need to stay home to provide care and make trips to the doctor.
o Children can spread diseases to newborns too young to have received all doses of recommended vaccines, or people with weakened immune systems, such as some people with cancer and transplant recipients who are also at higher risk of disease.
• For example, measles is still common in many parts of the world. The disease is brought into the United States by unvaccinated travelers who are infected while in other countries. When measles gets into communities of unvaccinated and under-vaccinated people in the U.S. (such as people who refuse vaccines for religious, philosophical or personal reasons), outbreaks are more likely to occur.
o The measles outbreak in 2015 was a perfect example of how quickly infectious diseases can spread when they reach groups of people who aren’t vaccinated.
o Since measles was declared eliminated in the United States in 2000, the annual number of people reported to have measles ranged from a low of 37 people in 2004 to a high of 668 people in 2014. In 2015, there were 189 provisionally reported cases.

* There is no research of how the shot affects pregnant women.
.

Lab group, meet world (most scientists don't do insta so this is a proxy meet). World, meet Cordwell lab group!
-
We are a split lab group. Half of us (including me) look at bacterial pathogenesis using combinatorial exploratory 'omics including genomics, proteomics, transcriptomics, lipidomics and metabolomics. In real English this means we look at whole cellular activity in every biological respect to inform vaccine/treatment discovery, with mass spectrometry as a mainstay of our technical toolkit.
-
The other half are involved in looking at myocardial ischaemia, investigating the progression of this condition through tissue pathology and post-translational modifications of key proteins through mass spectrometry. In real English this means heaps of excel sheets and I really don't envy what they do :face_with_tears_of_joy:.

If you're Dating someone with depression....
She's going to be tired. Constantly. Don't let her stay in bed
all day. She's not going to want to eat. Make her food any
way. She's going to want to cancel plans just to go home
and watch netflix. Take her out dancing any way. She will
look like she's not in the mood to be silly. Try to make her
laugh any way. She's going to want to cry over spilled
coffee. Don't make it seem like its not a big deal or that
she's being dramatic. She's going to be happy and sad at
the same time, and I know that sounds crazy but it's the
truth. She is going to need constant reassurance that she's
beautiful. Tell her. She is going to constantly need
reassurance that you're not going to leave her. She isn't
doubting you or questioning your love, depression comes
with anxiety. It comes with no appetite, sleeping 10 hours
and waking up tired. It comes with the illusion of standing in
a room with hundreds of people and being seen by none of
them. It doesn't make sense. It's impossible to understand
so imagine how they feel.... fighting a constant internal
battle. So be that support system. Reassure and love hard.
Never give up on her.

We had fewer learning disabilities, less asthma, less autism, and less diabetes.  Autism in particular was 1 in 500 in the late seventies and it has now skyrocketed to 1 in 50.  Why so many?  Why so soon?

I am so sorry that I didn’t know that the government has paid out $3billion to families injured by vaccines through the VICP (Vaccine Injury Compensation Program). And until recently, I had never heard of a CDC scientist/whistleblower named Dr. William Thompson (note, I can’t link to a story because even the article written in Forbes has been removed online). Within 8 days of their DPT vaccination, 11 infants died in Tennessee. Nine of the 11 had received DPT vaccine from Wyeth Laboratories lot 64201. Four of the 11 were dead in 24 hours.

All the deaths, which coroners classified as crib deaths (technically, sudden infant death syndrome), occurred between August 1978 and March 1979.

On April 26, 1979, the US surgeon general called for a meeting with officials from CDC, FDA, top DPT researchers and drug manufacturers.

CDC reported on a survey of states that had received 7,500 or more doses of lot 64201.

The survey yielded 14 more infant deaths — half within 24 hours of a DPT shot. All were classified as crib deaths. However, the children had received vaccine from other lots [in addition?]. Three years later, the first major article about the so-called Tennessee cluster appeared in the Journal of Pediatrics: "panel could not find a causal relationship between lot 64201 and crib death although it could not exclude one, either.” In Fresno County, Coroner Dr. David Hadden researched records from an unusual cluster of crib deaths in 1981.

http://www.whale.to/vaccines/fresno3.html

caption:
Did you know research led by Dr. Gina Ogilvie, an investigator at BC Children’s Hospital and BC Centre for Disease Control, shows that teen girls who receive the HPV vaccine are not more likely to be promiscuous?

The HPV vaccine has saved lives throughout the world by protecting against two strains of HPV that cause 70 per cent of cervical cancers. When the vaccine was introduced, some worried that it would lead to increased promiscuity among youth, but Dr. Ogilvie’s work shows there’s no evidence to support these concerns.

For International Women’s Day this week, go to the link in our bio to learn more about Dr. Ogilvie's research on the HPV vaccine.

@Regrann from @thehushreport -  Parents have another year to buy new car seats since the new law to require children younger than 2 to sit in rear-facing #childsafety seats while traveling in a motor vehicle does not take effect until 2017.

The #vaccination law eliminates the ability of parents to waive #immunization rules for their children based on #personalbeliefs. Tho the law takes effect Jan. 1, it allows parents to delay the vaccinations until July 1 if they filled out a request before #NewYearsDay. But almost all students will have to show proof of immunization for the start of the school year in the fall.

Starting Friday, the state #minimumwage will increase from $9 to $10 an hour.

The bill that garnered the most national attention will allow doctors to prescribe lethal doses of #drugs to #terminallyill patients. It will take effect 90 days after a special session on healthcare adjourns. That date has not yet been set, but the adjournment could happen as early as this month.

The #medicalmarijuana regulation bills become law Jan. 1, but a new licensing system doesn’t begin operating until 2018. 
Another new law will allow the state to automate #voterregistration, for those who are eligible, when they go to the #DMV to get their driver’s license. But the new process will not begin until work is completed on a new statewide voter database, which is expected in June.

#California will now allow #hoverboards to be ridden wherever bicycles are ridden; within bicycle lanes, pathways & roadways. 
Among the most significant new laws is one that makes regulatory changes requiring utilities to work toward meeting a target of having 50% of the #energy used in the state come from #renewable sources such as wind & solar power by the end of 2030. The law also makes changes to help the state double the energy efficiency savings by that year.

Jan. 1 also is the start date for a ban on #concealed #weapons on college campuses. It plugs a loophole in state law that prev banned guns by everyone except those with concealed weapon permits.

The new year also requires #lawenforcement agencies to obtain a #searchwarrant before looking at private emails, texts & #GPS data.

caption:
Time to wake up. Death & vaccine injury. 
Regranned from @vaccinesuncovered -  Sharing from another group, with permission from Owen's mother:
-
"I wanted to share my story because my hope is that no one else has to experience the pain in my heart every single day. My son Owen Matthew Stokes passed away October 25, 2017. He was born August 18, 2017 and was just 2 months old. He was born at term and weighed 8.8lbs. He was perfectly healthy in every way. He was only breastfed, or bottle fed breast milk while I was at work.  He always slept alone, on his back, with no blankets and had zero breathing or respiratory issues. He had never been sick. He received vaccines just 48 hours prior to his passing, he was given a combination of 8 different vaccines, which is the norm for a 2 month old.  The first day after his vaccines he was very tired and lethargic, didn’t seem himself. The second day, which is the day he passed away, he was in the care of his grandmother while I was at work. He wouldn’t take a bottle, and was inconsolable. He was tired but couldn’t sleep because he was in such pain. His grandmother thought that he was just having really bad gas... she finally got him down for a nap for the first time that day, sometime after 2pm...But he never woke up. She went to check on him about 30 min later and noticed he was blue, but he still felt warm to the touch, she called me and I was in the car on my way home from work, Owens father was in the car with me and he called 911 and I tried my best to walk her through CPR because I work in the medical field and I am certified.. I was about 10 min away from home and by the time I got there he was in the ambulance.......but he didn’t make it. My little boy died and I wasn’t there... The next time I got to hold him he was lifeless in my arms. And he didn’t go peacefully in his sleep, he suffered. :broken_heart: But yet we were told he died from SIDS. (Sudden Unexplained Infant Death Syndrome).
—

WARNING-INTRAVENOUS AND INTRAMUSCULAR USE
Severe reactions, including fatalities, lve occured during and inmediately after INTRAVENOUS
injection of phytonadione. even when precautions have been taken to dilute the phytonadione and to
avoid rapid infusion. Severe reactions. including fatalities. have also been reported following
INTRAMUSCULAR administration. Typically these severe reactions have resembled hypersensitivity
or auapliylaxis, including shock and cardiac and or respiratory arest. Some patients have exhibited these
severe reactions on receiving phytonadione for the first time. Therefore the INTRAVENOUS and
INTRAMUSCULAR routes should be restricted to those situations where the subeutaneous route is not
feasible and the serious risk involved is considered justified
DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
Whenever possible. Vitamin K Injection (Phytonadione Injectable Emulsion, USP) should be
given by the subeutaneous route. (See Box Warning.) When intravenous administration is

caption: Boys with masks. When I was growing up, I had a good friend who had #polio.  My sister and I would walk to school with her everyday; her and her little white boots with metal splints. She made some noise when she walked and we could always tell when she was coming around. Athough #polio had been eradicated through vaccine in the 1950s, some mothers didn't #vaccinate. It was a virus passed through physical contact so it was transferred easily between children at school. Parents would make some kids wear small bags of garlic around their necks in the 40's and 50's to keep the disease away. That didn't work, by the way. Oddly enough, this friend of mine went on to recover quite a bit of her prior function and became one of our middle and high school track stars. #polio #happyending #boyswithballs #antique #oddities #medical #diseases #drawing #graphite #art #garlicisntjustforvampires

#Repost @doctor_of_holistic_health with @repostapp. ・・・ #Vaccines #Epidemic After researching vaccinations, I came upon this book and recommend it to anyone who wants to know all about vaccines. It discusses the many controversies surrounding vaccines and is written by experts in the fields of ethics, #medicine, law, science, business and history, and backed by a wealth of documentation and research which delves into the following issues: • The right to vaccination choice • The ethics and constitutionality of vaccination mandates.
• Personal narratives of parents, children and soldiers who have suffered vaccine injury.
• Vaccine safety science and evidence-based medicine.
• Corrupting conflicts of interest in the national vaccine program.
• What should parents do? A review of eight advice books on vaccines that span the gamut.
Contributing author Michael Belkin, former director of the Hepatitis B Vaccine Project of the National Vaccine Center states, “If you doubt the existence of adverse reactions to vaccines, you must first examine with your own eyes the U.S. Food and Drug Administration’s Vaccine Adverse Events Reporting System (VAERS), which is available and searchable online at www.medalerts.org. As of March 11, 2011, VAERS listed 361,519  reports of vaccine adverse events. Former FDA commissioner David Kessler wrote in the Journal of the American Medical Association, that ‘only 1 percent of serious adverse events are reported to the FDA.’” Sadly Belkin's daughter died when she was only 5 WEEKS OLD after receiving the Hepatitis B vaccination. #doctorofholistichealth #holistichealth #vaccinesafety #naturalhealth #naturalmedicine #toxins #mercurypoisoning #consciousness #conscious #higherknowledge #ascension #SIDS #allergies #healthandwellness #healthtips #vaccination #autism

caption:
Aaaaaaaand I'm in writing mode. Back to manning the battle station at home while I try and pump out a first-author in the next few weeks!
-
It's been so long since I've written a paper that was mine (I have spent most of the last 2 years writing up collaborations that I've done as I go along). This paper I'm writing has also ballooned out to be the most whopping amount of data, the methods section alone is taking up >20 pages.
-
I'm overwhelmed but really excited to champion our new pipeline to completely characterise bacteria from genome to protein and everything in between (yes everything). Not to mention the phenotyping and infection modelling!
-
I've found it really hard to get back into writing from scratch. My normal "get in the zone" repertoire involves a hefty dose of rum. Unfortunately it's not longer summer and I have a life to attend to so that's not a good option! I need ideas - people of Instagram, feed me with ideas! How do you ease into your "creative zone?"

caption: The flu shot helps protect you from influenza. Influenza is a virus that affects the upper respiratory system. Influenza is NOT a stomach virus. Another misconception is that you can catch the flu from the flu shot. The immunization for influenza is not a live virus. I know the flu shot is one of the most controversial of all the vaccines because it's not always effective against every strain of the virus. However, more people die from the flu each year than from every other vaccine preventable illness COMBINED. The flu is not just a bad winter cold. The flu can be dangerous and deadly. #vaccinessavebro

caption:
Health conscious consumers often pore over product labels trying to avoid certain ingredients. But those labels can be incomplete. A new Silent Spring Institute study shows that everyday products contain a wide range of potentially harmful chemicals, including many that are not listed on product labels.

The study (link is external), published in the peer-reviewed journal Environmental Health Perspectives, marks the largest investigation that actually tested the products themselves for the presence of many suspect chemicals. All 50 different categories of conventional products contained some target chemicals. And the majority of the “alternative” products—marketed for having safer ingredients than their conventional counterparts—also contained chemicals of concern.

Investigators tested products for the presence of hormone disruptors that raise concerns for breast cancer, growth, and reproduction, as well as chemicals associated with asthma. They found the highest concentrations in vinyl products, such as shower curtains and pillow protectors, and fragranced products, such as dryer sheets, and sunscreens. Of the alternative sunscreens tested, the product with the highest number of target chemicals was actually one marketed for babies and children.

Silent Spring Institute’s earlier research, as well as the Centers for Disease Control’s biomonitoring studies, have found many of the study chemicals in people’s homes and bodies. Now this study adds information about where the exposures are coming from in everyday products.

caption: It's World Immunization Week! Immunization can protect against 25 different infectious agents or diseases, from infancy to old age, including diphtheria, measles, pertussis, polio and tetanus. The World Health Organization (WHO) estimates active immunization currently averts 2 to 3 million deaths every year. However 22.6 million infants worldwide are still missing out on basic vaccines, mostly in developing countries. Inadequate immunization coverage rates often result from limited resources, competing health priorities, poor management of health systems and inadequate surveillance. The goal of World Immunization Week is to raise public awareness of how immunization saves lives, and support people everywhere to get the vaccinations needed against deadly diseases for themselves and their children. #worldimmunizationweek #savechildren #savelives #vaccine #vaccines #virus #disease #prevent #prevention #closethegap #immunizationgap #immunization #awareness #personalizedcause #nowitspersonal #knowmore

EXCERPT: "On Nov. 19, 2018, the CDC created a task force to investigate the cause of AFM. According to CDC director Robert Redfield, MD, the 16-member Acute Flaccid Myelitis Task Force “will ensure that the full capacity of the scientific community is engaged and working together to provide important answers and solutions to actively detect, more effectively treat, and ultimately prevent AFM and its consequences.” The AFM Task Force met in Atlanta, Georgia and presented its initial report at the BSC public meeting on Dec. 6, 2018. Themes covered in the presentation included: ~ Important to have strong collaboration encompassing CDC, NIH, expert academic partners and health departments ~ Need for understanding CNS (central nervous system) damage: direct pathogen effects, immune response ~ Non-human primate model and other model systems may be useful ~ Continue work on pathogen detection ~ Review and summarize clinical phenotypes of cases ~ Strengthen case identification and surveillance ~Work with partners to optimize recognition of AFM ~ Utilize surveillance for risk factor and other studies ~ Strengthen and expand education and communication outreach ~ Implement natural history study to better understand pathogen(s), pathogenesis and long-term outcomes ~ Continue close dialogue with parents and families on a variety of issues ~ Medical record interoperability

Vaccination is very important for your child. It shields them from common but potentially deadly diseases. For instance, an influenza vaccine protects your child from getting the flu at a young age. Precious Moments Christian Academy is one in spreading awareness of the importance of getting a flu shot for children.

caption:
Zika is a disease caused by a virus/germ that spreads to people mostly by mosquito bites from areas such as Central & South America, the Caribbean, & Mexico or through intercourse with someone infected. Mosquitoes in L.A. County currently do not spread the disease. Avoid mosquitoes if visiting areas known for this disease. There is no medicine or vaccine to treat or prevent this disease. Symptoms of Zika are fever, joint pain, rash, red eyes and muscle pain beginning 3-7 days after being infected. Illness is usually mild with symptoms lasting a week. Most people infected have no symptoms at all. See your doctor if you think you or someone from your family has this disease. 
For more information, please visit http://publichealth.lacounty.gov/acd/vectorZika.htm
image_text:
ZIKA VIRUS KEY POINTS
Zika spreads to people mostly by mosquito bites. It
sometimes spreads through sexual contact. The disease is
found mainly in Central & South America, the Caribbean, &
Mexico.
Avoid mosquito bites if visiting areas known to have the
disease.
Mosquitoes in LA County currently don't spread this disease.
Pregnant women infected with Zika may be at risk of having a
baby with birth defects.
There is no medicine or vaccine to treat or prevent this
disease.
Symptoms of Zika are fever, joint pain, rash, red eyes and
muscle pain beginning 3-7 days after being infected. Illness is
usually mild with symptoms lasting up to a week. Most people
infected have no symptoms at all.
People are rarely hospitalized or die from this disease. See
your doctor if you think you or someone from your family has this
disease.

The chicken pox vaccine is a classic example of a symptomatically shedding vaccine virus. It has to be seen to be contagious.

caption:
Until the 1990s, the vaccine administered to children for #diphtheria #tetanus and #pertussis protection was the #DTP #vaccine, one of the first combination vaccines ever licensed by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration #FDA.  However, as a “whole-cell” vaccine (meaning that it contained the entire Bordetella pertussis organism rather than purified components), DTP had a significant downside—including published safety concerns dating back to the 1930s and widespread reports of neurological damage emanating from both the United States and other countries. By 1991, the Institute of Medicine cautiously reported that the evidence was “consistent with a possible causal relation between DTP vaccine and acute encephalopathy” [brain disease].
…characterized pertussis prevention as ‘an unresolved problem,’ noting the ‘progressive increase’ in pertussis incidence after introduction of the acellular vaccines and the need for ever more boosters.
To pacify a concerned public, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) advised a phase-out of the whole-cell vaccine around 1991, while promoting an “acellular” version called DTaP (diphtheria, tetanus and acellular pertussis). By 1997, the switch had taken place for all five doses in the series, recommended for infants and children at two, four, six and 15-18 months and 4-6 years. In the two decades since the changeover, however, the DTaP vaccine has been plagued by embarrassingly low effectiveness.
A 2018 article characterized pertussis prevention as “an unresolved problem,” noting the “progressive increase” in pertussis incidence after introduction of the acellular vaccines and the need for ever more boosters. Another recent commentary flatly stated that “pertussis is…not under control in any country” and that new types of pertussis vaccines are needed. #unitedstates

What is (PID)? Pelvic inflammatory disease 
Pelvic inflammatory disease (PID) is an infection of the female reproductive organs. It usually occurs when sexually transmitted bacteria spread from vagina to uterus, fallopian tubes or ovaries. ... The condition might be detected later if you have trouble getting pregnant or if you develop chronic pelvic pain.

Pelvic inflammatory disease many not produce any symptoms or signs (referred to as being asymptomatic). In other cases it can cause the following: * fever,
* lower abdominal or pelvic pain,
* increased or foul vaginal discharge,
* painful urination
* painful sexual intercourse
* Irregular bleeding. 
Classical Risk Factors includes
* Age (25yrs)
* Multiple sexual partners
* Having sex without a condom * Use it intrauterine device for contraception. * Previous history of PID/STI * Douching 
Pelvic inflammatory disease can be life-threatening in severe cases because there are than 100 thousand cases per year in Nigeria.

The treatment of pelvic inflammatory disease involves antibiotics directed against the organisms responsible for the disease. It is very important to treat PID & to prevent it from coming back. Treatment of PID reduces the risk of complications, including infertility.

"I wanted to share my story because my hope is that no one else has to experience the pain in my heart every single day. My son Owen Matthew Stokes passed away October 25, 2017. He was born August 18, 2017 and was just 2 months old. He was born at term and weighed 8.8lbs. He was perfectly healthy in every way. He was only breastfed, or bottle fed breast milk while I was at work.  He always slept alone, on his back, with no blankets and had zero breathing or respiratory issues. He had never been sick. He received vaccines just 48 hours prior to his passing, he was given a combination of 8 different vaccines, which is the norm for a 2 month old.  The first day after his vaccines he was very tired and lethargic, didn’t seem himself. The second day, which is the day he passed away, he was in the care of his grandmother while I was at work. He wouldn’t take a bottle, and was inconsolable. He was tired but couldn’t sleep because he was in such pain. His grandmother thought that he was just having really bad gas... she finally got him down for a nap for the first time that day, sometime after 2pm...But he never woke up. She went to check on him about 30 min later and noticed he was blue, but he still felt warm to the touch, she called me and I was in the car on my way home from work, Owens father was in the car with me and he called 911 and I tried my best to walk her through CPR because I work in the medical field and I am certified.. I was about 10 min away from home and by the time I got there he was in the ambulance.......but he didn’t make it. My little boy died and I wasn’t there... The next time I got to hold him he was lifeless in my arms. And he didn’t go peacefully in his sleep, he suffered. :broken_heart: But yet we were told he died from SIDS. (Sudden Unexplained Infant Death Syndrome).

@Regran_ed from @naturalparentsnetwork -  Why you should NEVER vaccinate against whooping cough 
It is impossible to become immune to a bacteria. Pertussis (whooping cough) is a bacteria. Tetanus is a bacteria. Diphtheria is a bacteria. 
Take whooping cough... injecting the bacteria into a person is just making them an a asymptomatic carrier of whooping cough.

This is why vaccine logic isn't logic...it's insanity. The idea is that the vaccine will decrease the risk of an active infection. There is a big problem with that idea. Anyone who is an asymptomatic carrier...and they are reexposed to that bacteria (like being around someone recently vaccinated) can trigger the dormant bacteria into an active infection. 
The CDC's own data called 'Pertussis surveillance report's' detail that you are between 4-8x more likely to develop whooping cough if you are fully vaccinated vs someone who is completely unvaccinated. Go look it up...its not hidden information. Whooping cough is on the rise because children receive 5 doses of the dtap vaccine. That's a lot of carriers of the bacteria.

She holds strong values of social justice, and has a long-standing interest in addressing global health inequities. Her research interests include health equity for marginalized populations, the social determinants of health, monitoring and evaluation, community-based participatory health research, and health promotion. caption: With the recent measles outbreak in the state of Washington, immunization has become a major topic of discussion. We had our own case of measles in the Hudson Valley not too long ago and it is a cause for concern. While Kiryas Joel is a community of people that refuse to get vaccinated, their is an entire movement of people that are refusing to get vaccinated. Many say “we’ll@it only hurts the individual that isn’t vaccinated, so why don’t people mind their own business?” In reality, vaccines work in two ways. The one way is that they protect the individual from getting sick from a particular disease. The other way is that it establishes something that is called “Herd Immunity” in which we see that, the more people that’s re vaccinated, the less chance there is for people that aren’t vaccinated to get sick. The sick and elderly are often advised not to get vaccinated if their immune system is not even strong enough to fight the dead/weakened version of the disease found in the vaccine. In the past, this wasn’t a major problem because so many people were vaccinated. Now, as the number of people that are vaccinated decreases, we see that herd immunity is deteriorating. This creates a medical ethics debate. Should healthy people be forced to be immunized for the sake of the population? #hudsonvalley #hudsonvalleybiology #vaccines #antivaxxers #measles

caption:
1963: Oral polio vaccine is licensed
Oral #polio #vaccine (OPV) was proven to stop person-to-person transmission of wild poliovirus. 
Today, wild poliovirus type 2 has not been detected anywhere since 1999 and the Global Commission for the Certification of Poliomyelitis Eradication declared this strain globally eradicated at its meeting in September 2015. 
Countries have therefore been preparing to remove the type 2 component from OPV, by switching from trivalent #OPV (containing all three serotypes) to bivalent OPV (containing only type 1 and 3 serotypes)

Today is the the @unitednations' 70th birthday! Happy #UN70! :birthday_cake::party_popper::balloon:
On this occasion, we look back on the WHO’s history and milestones we have achieved together for public health.
More milestones, link on our bio :backhand_index_pointing_up_medium_skin_tone: Photo: WHO/J. Schytte

It's #WorldImmunizationWeek!

Remember that the benefits of having children vaccinated for illnesses such as polio, measles, tetanus, diphtheria, and hepatitis-B still outweigh the risks.

caption:
Not all parenting is smiles, giggles and waterfights on a sunny day. Sometimes it's hard, unglamorous and exhausting.
Matthew has really been struggling to get back into his routine after holidays and Hazel had more vaccinations this week (#responsibleparenting) She's also going through a growth spurt and a bit of sleep regression.
This 'dream' combination has brought us tears, temperatures and a tired mama. 
It's like they have a silent agreement to take turns to sleep at night. 
Paul has been working nightshifts so I've been flying solo with them this week. 
This pic was taken at about 1am. Hazel had a fever and had vomited all over me, by the time I took this, she'd just stopped crying. 
I just thought that it was important to not just post the 'perfect moments' because it's just not always real. Shit does happen. 
There will be days where you have bright eyes and lipstick and others where you wonder whether you have enough energy to wash baby sick out of your hair and bra.
But even when it's hard, it's still worth it. Hard times will pass. Smiles will return. But you've just laid another brick in the wall of parenting, it's a strong wall that can never be knocked. The ultimate labour of love, if you'll let me get cheesy! To all parents rocking their children in the middle of the night wondering if you'll ever sleep properly again, hold tight. You rock x
.

caption:
I'm in no way saying that there aren't educated people deciding to vaccinate.

But I am saying that despite "anti-vaxers" and vaccine questioners being painted as anti-science, conspiracy theorists into quackery, the research is showing that "anti-vaxers" are actually all about science, logic and the evidence.

In Australia, low vaccination rates are amongst the wealthiest areas with the most educated people.

So, educated people are making decisions not to vaccinate because they look at the science and all the information. It shouldn't be such a controversial topic. It should be a conversation that everyone is willing to have for the good of society. 
Science is always about questioning, improving, finding new advancements. The attitude towards vaccination policy is the most backward example of science I've ever seen.

No questioning, no desire for improvements, it's apparently settled.

That's not science.

Happy #worldimmunizationweek! Edward Jenner introduced the first successful vaccine in 1796 when he followed his observation that milkmaids who had previously caught cowpox did not later catch smallpox. The term “vaccine” is derived from Variolae vaccinae meaning “smallpox of the cow,” which was used by Jenner to refer to cowpox. 
In 1980, following an historic global campaign of surveillance and vaccination, the World Health Assembly declared smallpox eradicated – the only infectious disease to achieve this distinction. #vaccineswork

caption:
*A break in normal posting, don't worry normal posting will resume when I can be arsed*

Some time ago I went to London with my beloved to spend the weekend. Whilst there I visited Hyde Park for the first time. And there I came across this monument of a man who changed the landscape of healthcare indefinitely. For the better. I am of course talking about one of the great pillars of public health, Edward Jenner. The father of vaccinations. You will undoubtedly read many many ‘Alternative Facts’ by anti-vaxxers. But as usual they tend to be more confined within the fiction section of third hand bookshops. Edward Jenner for those who don't know discovered that those infected with cowpox were invariably immune to smallpox, this started mass immunization programs. 
Without him there is a very good chance that we would still be having to deal with mass epidemics of deadly, dangerous, disfiguring illnesses like Smallpox, measles, polio and many many more. 
Edward Jenners variolation was as important as John Snow's sanitation investigation, Joseph Lister’s insistence on equipment sterilization, Ignaz Semmelweis preoccupation with the importance of hospital staffs handwashing. 
Vaccines save lives. 
Edward Jenner was a hero.

Did a more extensive blog at http://ingvararni.blogspot.com/2017/02/metal-nurse-edward-jenner-healthcare.html

Former CBS investigative journalist Sharyl Attkisson reports that the most recent statistics on vaccine injury settlements have officially been scrubbed from the federal government's vaccine "court" website, which is run by the Health Resources and Services Administration.

The so-called "adjudication" chart, which had previously been updated monthly, is now buried deep beneath several layers on the site, presenting only outdated statistics that make vaccines appear less damaging than they actually are. "Wiping the latest data means the 'adjudication' chart on a government website no longer reflects the recent, sharp rise in court victories for plaintiffs who claimed their children were seriously injured or killed by one or more vaccines," she wrote about the #coverup. "Since January of 2014, twice as many victims have won court decisions than the previous 8 years combined. In these court decisions, a judge ruled the evidence showed vaccines 'more likely than not' caused the plaintiff's injuries." Forget statistics: All you need to know is that vaccines are safe & effective!

So what, exactly, did the #feds put in place of the adjudication chart? Get this -- a message informing the public that vaccines are "safe & effective." No #science, no data, just more tired &empty rhetoric urging the public to just trust the government & forget all about #vaccinedamage & vaccine "court" disbursements.

The Independent Thinker's
VACCINES FACT SHEET
Modern medicine tells us we must
vaccinate our children. Vaccines are also
developed for adults. Most of us believe
these injections are "insurance policies" for
our health. The reality is that vaccinations
have never-in all of history-diminished the incidence of
disease. Here are 10 facts you should know.
1. Vaccines are made from live pathogens grown (or cultured) in animal blood, animal
tissue, chicken embryos and aborted human fetal cells
2. Vaccine cultures are preserved with neurotoxins such as mercury (thimerosal).
formaldehyde, phenol, aluminum and MSG. These toxic mixtures are directly injected
into babies,children and adults, bypessing the body's built-in filters (cilia, tonsils, skin)
3. Childhood vaccinations are the first assault on the normal functioning of the body
creating neurological damage and debiltating the immune system.
4. Today's children are routinely vaccinated by pediatricians performing what they
believe to be "preventive medicine. By age six, most children have been exposed to
more than 100 viral strains
5 Vaccines are frequently administered in combination, as in measlesimumps/rubella
(MMR), In nature itself one would never encounter this type of multiple viral load
6. With repeated injections, the damage caused by vaccines can lead to developmental
problems, auto-immune disease, sudden infant death (SIDS), autism and more.
7 One out of five American children now has special needs These include learning
disabilities, attention-deficit disorders and behavioral issues, creating a whole new
market for certain kinds of prescription drugs
8. Contrary to popular belief, parents are not legaly obligated to vaccinate their
children. Most states allow exemptions for medical, religious or philosophical reasons.
(Check your own state's laws)
9 Plagues such as smalpox and polio were never eradicated by vaccines. Smallpox
declined with improved sanitation, and polio persists under many new names.
10. The United States vaccinates more than any other country. Beware of future
pandemics and federal imposition of mandatory vaccinations.

Repost from @vintage_vegan_ using @RepostRegramApp - Author and alternative health practitioner Ann Boroch has died.

The Los Angeles County coroner’s department confirmed to us on 8 August 2017 that Boroch’s cause of death a week before was suicide by hanging. The department’s report identified her by her first name, Tami.

Boroch’s Facebook page announced her death on 4 August 2017, and the post was cross-linked to her Twitter account. A second Twitter post carried an additional message while also linking to her Facebook page: "Hi everyone! My name is Lisa and I am Ann’s cousin. I am sorry to say this is not a hoax or a joke. Thank you all…"
However, the Facebook page was taken down completely not long after that. Some web sites reporting on Boroch’s death included a screen capture of what was purportedly the original post:
"It is with a heavy heart we share with you that Ann Boroch, passed away suddenly on Tuesday, August 1, 2017.

Many of you are familiar with Ann’s story….. Throughout her early 20’s, she battled Multiple Sclerosis. “When traditional medicine provided no relief, she created her own self-help program and discovered that yeast and fungal toxins are the main culprits in autoimmune disease.

By diligently maintaining a strict candida diet, Ann was able to cure herself of MS. Grateful for the healing triumph, she realized that it had become her mission to educate the public.

Ann went back to school and became a naturopath, certified clinical hypnotherapist, and certified nutritional consultant. After that, Ann opened her own practice in Los Angeles, and for almost 20 years has been the guiding light to healing for thousands of people around the world." It is unclear why Boroch’s Facebook page was apparently taken down. However, Health Nut News founder Erin Elizabeth, who has for years pushed a narrative that dozens of alternative doctors and naturopaths have been dying under mysterious circumstances (a claim that we investigated and found lacked supporting evidence) got involved in the tragedy, saying in a video broadcast on her own Facebook page on 8 August 2017 that “everybody” was posting the

Aluminum is a well-known #neurotoxin that can have many adverse affects on your health. People are exposed to aluminum in a variety of ways, including medications, #vaccines, food, water, cosmetics, & hygienic products like #deodorant.
:globe_with_meridians:
Secret & many other commercial deodorants use aluminum as #antiperspirant, which clogs, closes, or blocks the pores that release sweat under your arms. Not only does this block one of your body's routes for detoxification from sweating but it raises concerns about where these metals go once applied to your skin.
:globe_with_meridians:
Aluminum has been proven to contribute to many health problems, including:

:small_blue_diamond:Ulcers
:small_blue_diamond:Anemia

Breast cancer is especially of concern regarding the use of aluminum-based antiperspirant, like Secret. Research, including a study in the Journal of Applied Toxicology, has shown that the aluminum is not only absorbed by your body, but deposited into breast tissue. In another study published in the Journal of Inorganic Biochemistry, researchers tested breast samples from 17 breast-cancer patients who had undergone #mastectomies. The women who used antiperspirants had deposits of aluminum in their outer breast tissue. Concentrations of aluminum were higher in the tissue closest to the underarm than in the central breast.
:globe_with_meridians:
Other studies have exposed a direct link between aluminum intake and Alzheimer's Disease. Aluminum is to your central nervous system as cigarette smoke is to your lungs. Scientists are clear that toxic metals damage brain tissue and lead to this degenerative disease.
:globe_with_meridians:
Secret is well aware of the dangers of using such a toxic ingredient in its products, but continues to use it with blatant disregard to the consumer's health. Opt for aluminum-free deodorants available on the market.  Join us in boycotting aluminum-based deodorants like Secret FOR GOOD!

image_text:
Is there such a thing as an autism gene?
Not really. There are several conditions
associated with autism that stem from
mutations in a single gene, including
fragile X and Rett syndromes. But less than
1 percent of non-syndromic cases of autism
stem from mutations in any single gene. So
far, at least, there is no such thing as an
‘autism gene’ — meaning that no gene is
consistently mutated in every person with
autism. There also does not seem to be any
gene that causes autism every time it is
mutated.

Sucralose was accidentally discovered while doing research to create a new insecticide, which is why some researchers suggested that sucralose should be listed in the insecticide category. This neurotoxin is regarded as a chemical cousin to DDT. Sucralose is a chlorinated compound. When the body breaks this type of chlorinated compound, it releases toxic chemicals.

Aluminum is hard for the body to absorb, but citrate or citric acid can dramatically increase its absorption. caption: Yesterday Josephine had a doctor appointment. Typically Owen and I either stay home and Mom and Jo go, or Owen and I go along, but we leave the room when she gets her shots. Yesterday Owen wanted Mom to leave with him. So I stayed in the room with Jo while she got her shot. The first picture is of her looking at the door as the nurses knocked to come in. She knew what was coming. The nurses came in, I set her down on the table and she immediately started crying. She grabbed both of my pointer fingers with both hands and squeezed tight to make sure I wouldn’t let her go. Broke my heart. Then when the nurses stuck the needles into her legs she screamed and cried even harder. Right when she was done I picked her up and she buried her head into my chest and cried until the nurses left. The second picture is right after the nurses left the room. She picked her head off of my chest and calmed down pretty quickly. We soon left the doctor and went to Piggly Wiggly where her and her brother got to ride in a car cart and she soon forgot all about the doctor. A few things that I am thankful for from yesterday: first, I have a job that allows me the opportunity to see my children grow more than most parents who work full time get. There is not much that I miss. Second, That we live in a country and a time period that has childhood immunizations. Might sound stupid, but think of all the things we don’t have to worry about as parents compared to 100 years ago. Jo got a shot of chicken pox for gosh sakes. That blew my mind. Finally, I am thankful that my little girl knew that it wasn’t me that was hurting her and grabbed onto me after like she knew I would never let anything bad happen to her. #jesseslentphotoproject #daddysgirl #vaccines #needlessuck #godfamilyandthegreenbaypackers

caption: "I was introduced to the community of Tetzilquila, a little village in the mountains of Mixtla de Altamirano near Orizaba, Veracruz.  To get there we drove several hours until there was no road, and then we hiked a couple more to get there.  When we got to the top after all that walking, there was nothing there!  I asked where the community was… it was down, another 800 meters, with no clear path marked through giant rocks, vegetation and slippery soil.  Finally, it was there in the bottom that we encountered a community of 40 families who did not speak Spanish – they still spoke the pure language of the Aztecs, called Nahuatl.  Only a few adults spoke Spanish.  Once there I could see the hard conditions they lived in and the poor status of nutrition in both the children and the adults.  Their leader told me through an interpreter that they had to walk many miles to go to the closest little town to buy their needs, but then they had to walk even farther to get basic medical care.  I had the interpreter (who came with us) ask the mothers about their priorities and current problems.  Little by little their shyness disappeared and they started talking one by one.  It was an incredible experience to hear them talk about children getting sick, some diseases they suffered and their needs.  As they spoke more I found that I could understand a lot of what they were saying.  The interpreter was surprised and I was surprised; but I learned from the experience that motherhood is universal and did not need a language to communicate.  I fell in love with this community and knew I found a place to start a clinic." - @felisahilbert Full interview link in profile #InspiringWomen #VaccinesWork #WorldImmunizationWeek @shotatlife #Mexico

1. WHAT IS MEASLES?
AA
2. WHAT ARE THE RISKS?
Measles is a self-limiting childhood viral infection.
• Measles symptoms include a prodromal (initial) phase
of cough, runny nose, eye irritation and fever, followed
by a generalized rash on days 4-10 of the illness.
Measles is contagious during the prodromal phase
and for 3-4 days after rash onset.
In the modern era, it is rare to suffer permanent
disability or death from measles in the United
States. Between 1900 and 1963, the mortality rate of
measles dropped from 13.3 per 100,000 to 0.2
per 100,000 in the population, due to advancements
in living conditions, nutrition, and health care-
a 98% decline (Fig. 1).25 Malnutrition, especially
vitamin A deficiency, is a primary cause of about
90,000 measles deaths annually in underdeveloped
nations. In the US, and other developed countries,
75-92% of hospitalized measles cases are low in
vitamin A
• Most measles cases are benign and not reported
to public health departments.
Before the measles mass vaccination program was
introduced, nearly everyone contracted measles and
obtained lifetime immunity by age 15
Research studies and national tracking of measles
have documented the following:
• In rare situations, measles can cause brain damage
and death.
Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)
publishes measles case-fatality rates based on reported
cases. However, nearly 90% of measles cases are benign
and not reported to the CDC2 Calculating case-fatality
rates based on reported cases (that constitute only 10%
of all cases) results in a case-fatality rate that is 10 times
higher than what it actually is in the general population
Data analysis herein is based on total measles cases
(both reported and unreported)
• 1 in 10,000 or 0.01% of measles cases are fatal
• 3 to 3.5 in 10,000 or 0.03-0.035% of measles
cases result in seizure.
• 1 in 20,000 or 0.005% of measles cases result in
measles encephalitis.
• 1 in 80,000 or 0.00125% of cases result in per-
manent disability from measles encephalitin.
• 7 in 1,000 or 0.7% of cases are hospitalized.
.6 to 22 in 1,000,000 or 0.0006-0.0022% of
cases result in subacute sclerosing pan-
encephalitis (SSPE)

Vaccines are crucial during antenatal days. It is highly recommended to follow your schedules given by your Gynechologist/Hospital to avoid potential infections to the foetus during pregnancy and in the early days of life. Schedules differ in different parts of the world and keeps getting updated based on many factors including susceptibility, weather conditions, epidemics, etc,. So, do not skip a vaccine simply comparing your schedule to another's. Take special attention if you are planning to travel (to a far off region or another country). Talk to your health care providers incase of doubts. Have a healthy and risk-free pregnancy.

Polio was a scourge, and had been infecting humans around the world for millennia. Immunization are always a hot topic for conversations. Continuing with a part two:
If you choose to NOT immunize, there are some things that, in my opinion, MUST be considered that are often overlooked:
:sparkles:please, make an informed choice:
research the side effects of diseases you are choosing to skip the immunizations for. Don't do it because a lovely neighbor next door said it's bad - check your facts.
Look for real life experiences, NOT just stats. Numbers are dry. Look at situations real people experienced. Loosing a child or having a child get hurt due to side-effects of improperly administered vaccines is real. Loosing a child or having a child get hurt because of side-effects of a preventable disease is real too. Very real. :sparkles: ENSURE you look at "what if?" and see what treatments are available for diseases. It's a common misconception in the "anti-vaccine" camps that medicine knows it all and can easily treat everything today. NOT everything. Some things can be prevented, but not treated.
:sparkles: As parents, we should always work hard to give our kids best health possible. It is 100x more important that kids have very strong immune systems when not immunized. Bodies are smart, that is true, but they need to be in an excellent condition to fight what's around us. We can do a separate post on helping kids build immune system.
:sparkles: Being smart and responsible is very important - traveling the world in the heat of flu outbreak is not the best idea ( amazingly shocking how many people think the opposite). Take preventative measures too - I had a couple of posts on travel, I can write more. It's not 100% perfect, but i feel it helps.
:sparkles: Knowing EARLY symptoms of all life-threatening diseases and watching for them constantly is very important. Immunized people can actually be disease carriers without harm to themselves, so being on a constant watch is important.
:sparkles:Having a flexible state of mind and staying on top of medical research is very important. Medicine is moving forward, new things are constantly discovered and utilized. What was bad yesterday can have an adjusted formula tomorrow. Keep in mind, though, :backhand_index_pointing_down_light_skin_tone:

caption:
There are 2 types of vaccines: recombinant vaccines (Engerix B:registered:, GenHevac B:registered:, HBvaxpro:registered:, etc.) and human plasma-derived vaccines (Heptavax:registered:, etc.)
Solution for injection, in single-dose syringe or multidose vial, for IM injection into the deltoid muscle (into the anterolateral part of the thigh in children under 2 years
.
.
• Contra-indications, effets indesirables, precautions:-
Do not administer to patients with hypersensitivity to any component of the vaccine, or history of an allergic  reaction to a previous injection. Vaccination should be postponed in the event of severe acute febrile illness (minor infections are not contra-indications).
Do not administer into the gluteal region (diminished antibody response to vaccine).
In patients with multiple sclerosis, assess the benefit-risk balance of vaccination.

May cause:
• minor local or general reactions (pain or redness at injection site, fever, headache,  myalgia, etc.),
• very rarely: anaphylactic reaction, serum disease, lymphadenopathy, peripheral neuro-pathy.
Shake before use to homogenise the vaccine.
Do not mix with other vaccines in the same syringe (inactivation of vaccines).
If administered simultaneously with EPI vaccines, use different syringes and injection sites.
Pregnancy : only administer if there is a high risk of contamination
Breast-feeding : no contra-indication.
.
.
• Remarks:-
Immunity develops 1 to 2 months after the 3 rd injection. Vaccine efficacy is > 80%.
If the vaccination schedule is interrupted before the complete series has been administered,
it is not necessary to start again from the beginning. Continue the vaccination schedule from where it was interrupted and complete the series as normal.
SC route may be used, only if IM route is contra-indicated.
Storage : between 2°C and 8°C - Do not freeze
.
.
